Target: OntoCompMat is an ontology developed for representing composite composite materials.

Comment: A material consisting of two or more distinct phases bonded together (Comprehensive Composite Materials, 2000). A composite material is composed from at least two materials, where one is the reinforcing material and other is the matrix material (Advanced Composite Materials for Automotive Applications, 2013).
Label: Composite Material

Comment: A material with a solid structure manufactured from a single material (Construction and Building Materials, 2023).
Label: Monolithic Material

Comment: A composite material in which the type of matrix plays a key role in determining the mechanical, thermal, chemical, and electrical properties of the composite.
Label: Composite Based on Matrix Material

Comment: A composite material in which the matrix is based on polymer.
Label: Polymer matrix composite

Comment: A composite material in which the matrix is based on metal.
Label: Metal matrix composite

Comment: A composite material in which the matrix is based on ceramic.
Label: Ceramic matrix composite

Comment: A composite material in which the matrix is based on carbon or graphite.
Label: Carbon matrix composite

Comment: A composite material in which the matrix material is a thermoplastic polymer.
Label: Thermoplastic matrix composite

Comment: A composite material in which the matrix material is a thermosetting polymer.
Label: Thermoset matrix composite

Comment: A carbon matrix composite in which carbon fibres are embedded in the matrix.
Label: Carbon–carbon composite

Comment: A thermoset matrix composite where the matrix is built with epoxy.
Label: Epoxy Based Composite

Comment: A thermoset matrix composite where the matrix is built with phenolic resin.
Label: Phenolic Based Composite

Comment: A thermoset matrix composite where the matrix is built with melamine resin.
Label: Melamine Based Composite

Comment: A thermoset matrix composite where the matrix is built with polyester resin.
Label: Polyester Based Composite

Comment: A thermoplastic matrix composite where the matrix is built with polyetheretherketone resin.
Label: Polyetheretherketone Based Composite

Comment: A thermoplastic matrix composite where the matrix is built with polypropylene resin.
Label: Polypropylene Based Composite

Comment: A thermoplastic matrix composite where the matrix is built with polyethylene resin.
Label: Polyethylene Based Composite

Comment: A thermoplastic matrix composite where the matrix is built with acrylonitrile butadiene styrene resin.
Label: Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene Based Composite

Comment: A composite known by the manufacturing technique applied in its production.
Label: Manufacturing Process Based Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the hand lay-up process.
Label: Hand Lay-Up Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the pultrusion process.
Label: Pultrusion Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the filament winding process.
Label: Filament Winding Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the injection molding process.
Label: Injection Molding Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the resin transfer molding process.
Label: Resin Transfer Molding Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the compression molding process.
Label: Compression Molding Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the vacuum infusion process.
Label: Vacuum Infusion Composite

Comment: A composite produced with the autoclave process.
Label: Autoclave Composite

Comment: A composite known by the orientation of its reinforcement fibres.
Label: Orientation Based Composite

Comment: A composite that has reinforcement fibres aligned parallel to the primary load path.
Label: Longitudinal Orientation

Comment: A composite that has reinforcement fibres arranged perpendicular to the primary load path.
Label: Transverse Orientation

Comment: A composite that has reinforcement fibres arranged in multiple directions.
Label: Random Orientation

Comment: A composite that has reinforcement fibres arranged in a single, uniform direction.
Label: Unidirectional Orientation

Comment: A composite that has reinforcement fibres aligned exactly parallel to the primary load path.
Label: 0 Degree Orientation

Comment: A composite that has reinforcement fibres aligned perpendicular to the primary load path.
Label: 90 Degree Orientation

Comment: A composite known by the function it serves in applications.
Label: Functional Requirement Based Composite

Comment: A composite that provides structural support for load bearing, strength, stiffness, etc. in applications.
Label: Structural Composite

Comment: A composite designed to function as a barrier, halting the passage of chemicals, liquids, and gases, in applications.
Label: Barrier Composite

Comment: A composite designed to manage heat by functioning as in insulator, conductor, or thermal resistor in applications.
Label: Thermal Composite

Comment: A composite designed to control electromagnetic fields through shielding or absorption in applications.
Label: Electromagnetic Composite

Comment: A composite designed to carry mechanical loads in applications for structural functions.
Label: Load Bearing Composite

Comment: A composite designed to function as a force or shock absorber in applications.
Label: Impact Resistant Composite

Comment: A composite designed to function as a barrier, halting vapor transmission in applications.
Label: Vapor Barrier Composite

Comment: A composite designed to function as a barrier, halting gas transmission in applications.
Label: Gas Barrier Composite

Comment: A composite designed to manage heat by functioning as an insulator in applications.
Label: Thermal Insulation Composite

Comment: A composite designed to manage heat by transfering it away to control overheating in applications.
Label: Heat Dissipating Composite

Comment: A composite designed to control electromagnetic fields through shielding in applications.
Label: Electromagnetic Shielding Composite

Comment: A composite designed to control electromagnetic fields through absorption in applications.
Label: Electromagnetic Absorbing Composite

Comment: A composite known by the type of fibre applied for reinforcement.
Label: Fibre Type Based Composite

Comment: A composite that uses glass fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Glass Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses carbon fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Carbon Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses aramid fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Aramid Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses silicon fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Silicon Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses boron fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Boron Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses inorganic fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Inorganic Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses alumina fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Alumina Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that uses aluminosilicate fibre as reinforcement in the matrix.
Label: Aluminosilicate Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite known by its internal structural configuration.
Label: Structure Based Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged like textile weaving.
Label: Woven Structure Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged randomly without following any weaving or knitting structure.
Label: Non Woven Structure Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged in interlooped patterns.
Label: Knitted Structure Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are interlaced in a criss-cross patterns.
Label: Braided Structure Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged in a simple over-under pattern.
Label: Plain Weave Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged in a diagonal-parallel pattern.
Label: Twill Weave Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged in an over-under pattern interlacing after a few yarns.
Label: Satin Weave Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged in groups of two or more, following an over-under pattern like weaving.
Label: Basket Weave Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement longitudinal (warp) fibres are twisted over and under the tranverse (weft) fibres.
Label: Leno Weave Woven Composite

Comment: A composite which imitates the structure of a leno weave woven composite except for the twisting of warp fibres.
Label: Mock Leno Weave Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged randomly in a mat form without stiching or adhesives.
Label: Fibre Mat Non Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged randomly and stitched together.
Label: Stitch Bonded Non Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged randomly and bonded together with adhesive.
Label: Adhesively Bonded Non Woven Composite

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement fibres are arranged in a two directional braided structure.
Label: Biaxial Braided Composite

Comment: A composite that has the reinforcement fibres arranged in two opposing directional braided structures with fibres set along the axis.
Label: Triaxial Braided Composite

Comment: A composite that has the reinforcement fibres arranged in a braided tube-like structure.
Label: Tubular Braided Composite

Comment: A composite that has the reinforcement fibres orthogonally arranged, forming a grid like structure.
Label: Cartesian Braided Composite

Comment: A composite that applies aluminum alloy as the matrix material.
Label: Aluminium Matrix Composite

Comment: A composite that applies magnesium alloy as the matrix material.
Label: Magnesium Matrix Composite

Comment: A composite that applies titanium alloy as the matrix material.
Label: Titanium Matrix Composite

Comment: A composite that applies silicon carbide as the matrix material.
Label: Silicon Carbide Matrix Composite

Comment: A composite that applies oxide as the matrix material.
Label: Oxide Matrix Composite

Comment: A composite that applies polyetheretherketone resin as the matrix material.
Label: Polyetheretherketone

Comment: A composite that applies polypropylene resin as the matrix material.
Label: Polypropylene

Comment: A composite that applies polyethylene resin as the matrix material.
Label: Polyethylene

Comment: A composite that applies acrylonitrile butadiene styrene resin as the matrix material.
Label: Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene

Comment: An additive applied to a composite matrix to enhance its mechanical, physical, and thermal properties.
Label: Filler Material

Comment: A material embedded in a composite matrix to carry loads and enhance mechanical properties, e.g., strength and stiffness.
Label: Reinforcement Material

Comment: Calcium Carbonate is a filler material applied to a composite matrix to improve its stiffness, dimensional stability, etc.
Label: CaCO3

Comment: Talc is a filler material applied to a composite matrix to improve its stiffness, dimensional stability, thermal resistance, etc.
Label: Talc

Comment: Wollastonite is a filler material applied to a composite matrix to improve its stiffness, dimensional stability, thermal conductivity, etc.
Label: Wollastonite

Comment: Glass fibre is a reinforcement material embedded in a composite matrix to improve strength, stiffness, and impact reistance properties.
Label: Glass Fibre

Comment: Carbon fibre is a reinforcement material embedded in a composite matrix to improve strength, stiffness, and fatigue reistance properties.
Label: Carbon Fibre

Comment: A manufacturing technique or method employed to produce composite parts by combining matrix and reinforcement materials to achieve desired properties.
Label: Composite Processing Technique

Comment: A composite processing technique that injects a molten composite material into a mould to provide it with the required shape.
Label: Injection Moulding

Comment: A composite processing technique that produces parts by heating and compressing glass mat sheets.
Label: Glass Mat Thermoplastic Compression Moulding

Comment: A composite processing technique that places dry reinforcement fibres in a closed mould, with liquid resin injected to impregnate and cure the fibres into shape.
Label: Resin Transfer Moulding

Comment: A composite processing technique that enables two or more liquids to react inside a mould and cure to form composites.
Label: Reaction Injection Moulding

Comment: A composite processing technique that heats thermoplastic composite sheets to form them into a required shape in a mould.
Label: Thermoforming

Comment: A composite processing technique in which a mould is covered with reinforcement fibres, which are impregnated with resin.
Label: Wet Lay Up Processes

Comment: A composite processing technique in which material profiles are formed by drawing continuous fibres through resin and a heated die.
Label: Pultrusion Process

Comment: A composite processing technique in which fibres are impregnated, wound around a mandreal, and cured.
Label: Filament Winding Process

Comment: A composite processing technique in which fibre mats are laid into a heated mould and compressed to from a shape.
Label: Compression Moulding Process

Comment: A composite processing technique in which vacum pressure is used to draw resin into dry fibre laid into a mould.
Label: Vacuum Infusion Process

Comment: A curing process in which laid composites are cured by applying heat and pressure.
Label: Autoclave Process

Comment: A composite processing technique in which the reinforcement fibres cover a mould, resin is applied to them, and the lay-up is exposed to the environment during processing.
Label: Open mould process

Comment: A composite processing technique in which the reinforcement fibres cover a mould, resin is applied to them, and the lay-up is kept in a closed environemnt during processing.
A composite processing technique in which a mould is manually covered with reinforcement fibres, which are impregnated with resin by hand.
Label: Hand Lay Up Process

Comment: A composite processing technique in which chopped fibres and resin are sprayed together and subsequently rolled to produce compacted laminate.
Label: Spray Up

Comment: A filament winding process in which wound fibres are longitudinally aligned with the mandreal.
Label: Axial Filament Winding

Comment: A filament winding process in which wound fibres form a helical pattern around the mandreal.
Label: Helical Filament Winding

Comment: A filament winding process in which wound fibres are perpendicular to the axis of the mandreal.
Label: Radial Filament Winding

Comment: A compression moulding process in which both heat and pressure are applied in a mould.
Label: Hot Press Compression Moulding

Comment: A compression moulding process in which both heat and vacuum pressure are applied in a mould.
Label: Vacuum Assisted Compression Moulding

Comment: A composite processing technique in which vacum pressure is used to draw resin into dry fibre laid into a mould covered with a vacuum bag.
Label: Vacuum Bagging Infusion

Comment: A composite processing technique in which vacum pressure is used to draw resin into dry fibre laid into a closed mould to impregnate and cure the fibres into shape.
Label: Vacuum Assisted Resin Transfer Moulding

Comment: An autoclave process where composites are cured under high pressure.
Label: High Pressure Autoclave Moulding

Comment: An autoclave process where composites are cured under high temperature.
Label: High-Temperature Autoclave Moulding

Comment: A composite known by the type or configuration of the reinforcement applied.
Label: Reinforcement Based Composite Material

Comment: A composite where particles are used as the reinforcement material.
Label: Particle Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite where fibres are used as the reinforcement material.
Label: Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A fibre reinforced composite where continuous fibres are used as the reinforcement material.
Label: Continuous Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A fibre reinforced composite where short fibres are used as the reinforcement material.
Label: Short Fibre Reinforced Composite

Comment: A particle reinforced composite in which single-crystal whiskers are used as the reinforcement material.
Label: Whisker Reinforced Composite

Comment: A particle reinforced composite in which particles are used as the reinforcement material.
Label: Particulate Reinforced Metal Matrix Composite

Comment: A structural composite in which two strong outer facing sheets bonded to a lightweight core.
Label: Sandwich Composite

Comment: A structural composite in which multiple layers of reinforcement and matrix materials are stacked.
Label: Laminated Composite

Comment: A composite that consists of a thermoplastic matrix material and reinforcement materials.
Label: Thermoplastic Matrix Reinforced Composite

Comment: A composite that consists of a thermoset matrix material and reinforcement materials.
Label: Thermoset Matrix Reinforced Composite

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantages of composite materials over monolithic materials.
Label: hasAdvantageOver

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of higher strength of composite materials over monolithic materials.
Label: hasRelativelyHigherStrengthThan

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of lower weight of composite materials over monolithic materials.
Label: hasRelativelyLowerWeightThan

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of excellent corrosion resistance of composite materials over monolithic materials.
Label: hasExcellentCorrosionResistanceOver

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of excellent thermal properties of composite materials over monolithic materials.
Label: hasExcellentThermalPropertiesOver

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of excellent dimensional stability of composite materials over monolithic materials.
Label: hasExcellentDimensionalStabilityOver

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of greater  impact resistance of composite materials compared to monolithic materials.
Label: hasMoreImpactResistanceThan

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of more fatigue resistance of composite materials compared to monolithic materials.
Label: hasMoreFatigueResistanceThan

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of more static load resistance of composite materials compared to monolithic materials.
Label: hasMoreResistanceToStaticLoadThan

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the advantage of more dynamic load resistance of composite materials compared to monolithic materials.
Label: hasMoreResistanceToDynamicLoadThan

Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the constituent material of laminated composite.
Label: consistsOf

Range: Calcium Carbonate UNION Talc UNION Wollastonite
Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the filler materials incorporated into a polymer composite material.
Label: hasFiller

Range: Injection Moulding UNION Glass Mat Thermoplastic Compression Moulding UNION Resin Transfer Moulding Process UNION Reaction Injection Moulding
Comment: An object property that describes knowledge about the processing techniques can be applied in producing different types of polymer composite materials.
Label: hasProcessingTechnique

Comment: A composite in which the reinforcement is based on textile structures.
Label: Textile Composite

Comment: A textile composite reinforced with woven fabrics.
Label: Woven Fabric Composite

Comment: A textile composite reinforced with braided fabrics.
Label: Braided Fabric Composite

Comment: A textile composite reinforced with knitted fabrics.
Label: Knitted Fabric Composite

Comment: Hybrids consist of several layers of composites and other types of materials, such as aluminium. The aluminium layer is reinforced by laminated or unidirectional (UD) composites composites. A hybrid composite may consist of two or more types of reinforcement or matrix materials.
Label: Hybrid Composite

Comment: Aspects to consider when manufacturing or recycling a composite material.
Label: Factor

Comment: The aspect that focuses on the distribution of fibres within the matrix material of a composite.
Label: Fibre Distribution in Matrix

Comment: The aspect that focuses on the degree of compatibility between the matrix and reinforcement materials.
Label: Compatibility between Matrix and Fibre

Comment: The aspect that describes the directional alignment of fibres within a composite material.
Label: Fibre Orientation

Comment: The aspect that focuses on the ability of fibres to withstand degradation at higher temperatures.
Label: Thermal Stability of Fibre

Comment: An object property that relates a factor influencing the manufacturing or processing of a polymer composite material.
Label: affectsProcessingAndManufacturingOf

Comment: An object property that describes the use of the thermoforming technique in the production of fibre mat non woven composite.
Label: isUsedToProduce
